<paragraph pageId="780" pageNumber="781">
About 120 species (Lorenz 2005: 438-439), mainly in the tropical regions, arrayed in five genera. Only one endemic species (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Perigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Perigona pallipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is found in North America and one in Europe (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assmann" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Galiciotyphlotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="780" pageNumber="781" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weberi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="780" pageNumber="781">Galiciotyphlotes weberi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Assmann from northwestern Spain).
</paragraph>
